definitions.definition: The master of the servants of a household ; ( historical ) the master of a feudal manor

subdefinitions.definition: The male head of a household , a father or husband .
The owner of a house , piece of land , or other possession

definitions.definition: One possessing similar mastery over others ; ( historical ) any feudal superior generally ; any nobleman or aristocrat ; any chief , prince , or sovereign ruler ; in Scotland, a male member of the lowest rank of nobility (the equivalent rank in England is baron )

subdefinitions.definition: A feudal tenant holding his manor directly of the king
A peer of the realm , particularly a temporal one
A baron or lesser nobleman , as opposed to greater ones

definitions.definition: One possessing similar mastery in figurative senses ( esp. as lord of ~)

subdefinitions.definition: A magnate of a trade or profession .

definitions.definition: The heavenly body considered to possess a dominant influence over an event , time , etc.

definitions.label_groups: British , Australia , via Cockney rhyming slang , obsolete
